-- 29-bootstrapper.cell
-- Tests: zero-to-many cell spawning, вҠўвҠў dynamic frontier growth, вҠўвҲҳ convergence
--        loop, meta-reasoning about what cells to create, synthesis from
--        heterogeneous spawned results
--
-- Start with ZERO cells beyond the meta-cell itself. The meta-cell reads a
-- natural language task, decides what cells are needed, spawns them via вҠўвҠў,
-- reads their results, identifies gaps, spawns more. вҠўвҲҳ loop until the
-- problem is solved.
--
-- Task: "Plan a weekend trip to Tokyo for someone who loves ramen and architecture"

вҠў task
  given prompt вүЎ "Plan a weekend trip to Tokyo for someone who loves ramen and architecture"
  yield prompt

  вҠЁ prompt is a concrete problem statement requiring multi-faceted planning

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- PHASE 1: Analyze task and decide what capabilities are needed
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠў analyze-needs
  given taskвҶ’prompt
  yield needed-cells[], rationale

  вҲҙ Read В«taskвҶ’promptВ» carefully. This is a blank slate вҖ” no cells exist yet.
    Decide what specialist cells are needed to solve this problem.
    For each needed cell, specify:
    - A name (kebab-case)
    - What it should do (one sentence)
    - What inputs it needs (from other cells or from the task)
    - What outputs it produces

    Think about what KINDS of knowledge/research are needed:
    - Domain expertise (ramen spots, architecture landmarks)
    - Logistics (transport, timing, neighborhoods)
    - Synthesis (combining into a coherent plan)
    - Validation (checking feasibility, conflicts)

  вҠЁ length(needed-cells) вүҘ 3
  вҠЁ needed-cells collectively cover the full scope of the task
  вҠЁ each needed-cell has name, purpose, inputs, outputs
  вҠЁ at least one cell depends on another's output (not all independent)

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- PHASE 2: Spawn specialist cells from nothing
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠўвҠў spawn-specialists
  given analyze-needsвҶ’needed-cells
  given taskвҶ’prompt
  given В§specialist-template
  yield В§specialist-cells[]
  until length(specialist-cells) = length(analyze-needsвҶ’needed-cells)
  max 8

  вҲҙ For each entry in В«analyze-needsвҶ’needed-cellsВ», instantiate a specialist
    cell from В«В§specialist-templateВ». Bind each cell's purpose and scope from
    the needed-cell specification. The cells execute independently вҖ” they each
    research or reason about their slice of the problem.

  вҠЁ one specialist cell per needed-cell
  вҠЁ each specialist cell has a distinct, non-overlapping scope

вҠў specialist-template
  given purpose
  given scope
  given taskвҶ’prompt
  yield findings, recommendations[]

  вҲҙ You are a specialist focused on: В«purposeВ».
    Your scope within the overall task В«taskвҶ’promptВ» is: В«scopeВ».

    Research and reason about your domain. Produce:
    - findings: what you discovered (facts, options, considerations)
    - recommendations: specific actionable items for the final plan

    Be concrete. Name real places, give real times, cite real constraints.

  вҠЁ findings is substantive (not a restatement of the task)
  вҠЁ length(recommendations) вүҘ 2
  вҠЁ recommendations are specific and actionable (names, addresses, times)

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- PHASE 3: Synthesize results from spawned cells
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠў synthesize
  given specialist-*вҶ’findings
  given specialist-*вҶ’recommendations
  given taskвҶ’prompt
  yield draft-plan, coverage-map

  вҲҙ Read ALL specialist findings and recommendations. Synthesize into a
    coherent draft plan for В«taskвҶ’promptВ».

    The draft-plan should be a structured weekend itinerary:
    - Day 1 and Day 2 with time blocks
    - Specific places, travel between them, meal times
    - Weave ramen and architecture throughout

    The coverage-map should note which aspects of the task are covered
    and which have gaps (missing information, unresolved conflicts,
    logistical unknowns).

  вҠЁ draft-plan covers both days of the weekend
  вҠЁ draft-plan includes at least 3 ramen spots and 3 architecture sites
  вҠЁ coverage-map identifies any remaining gaps

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- PHASE 4: Evaluate completeness вҖ” is the problem solved?
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠў evaluate-completeness
  given synthesizeвҶ’draft-plan
  given synthesizeвҶ’coverage-map
  given taskвҶ’prompt
  yield is-complete, gaps[], quality-score

  вҲҙ Evaluate whether В«synthesizeвҶ’draft-planВ» fully solves В«taskвҶ’promptВ»:
    1. Does it cover both days with realistic timing?
    2. Are ramen recommendations specific (not generic "find a ramen shop")?
    3. Are architecture sites specific and visitable on a weekend?
    4. Is travel between locations feasible (not zigzagging across the city)?
    5. Are there practical details (budget hints, reservation needs, transit)?

    Score quality 1-10. Mark is-complete = true only if quality вүҘ 7
    and no critical gaps remain.

  вҠЁ is-complete вҲҲ { true, false }
  вҠЁ quality-score вҲҲ 1..10
  вҠЁ if not is-complete then length(gaps) вүҘ 1
  вҠЁ gaps are specific and addressable (not vague "needs more detail")

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- PHASE 5: Gap-filling вҖ” spawn MORE cells for what's missing
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠўвҠў spawn-gap-fillers
  given evaluate-completenessвҶ’gaps
  given synthesizeвҶ’draft-plan
  given taskвҶ’prompt
  given В§gap-filler-template
  yield В§gap-filler-cells[]
  until length(gap-filler-cells) = length(evaluate-completenessвҶ’gaps)
  max 5

  вҲҙ For each gap in В«evaluate-completenessвҶ’gapsВ», spawn a cell that
    specifically addresses that gap. The cell receives the current
    draft-plan as context so it can fill in what's missing without
    contradicting what's already planned.

  вҠЁ one gap-filler cell per gap
  вҠЁ each gap-filler addresses a specific identified gap

вҠў gap-filler-template
  given gap-description
  given draft-plan-context
  given taskвҶ’prompt
  yield additional-findings, patch-recommendations[]

  вҲҙ You are filling a gap in an existing plan for В«taskвҶ’promptВ».
    The current draft plan: В«draft-plan-contextВ»
    The gap you must address: В«gap-descriptionВ»

    Research this specific gap and provide:
    - additional-findings: new information that fills the gap
    - patch-recommendations: specific additions/changes to the draft plan

    Do NOT contradict the existing plan. ADD to it or REFINE it.

  вҠЁ additional-findings directly addresses the gap
  вҠЁ patch-recommendations are compatible with the existing draft plan
  вҠЁ length(patch-recommendations) вүҘ 1

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- PHASE 6: Re-synthesize with gap-filler results
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠў re-synthesize
  given synthesizeвҶ’draft-plan
  given gap-filler-*вҶ’additional-findings
  given gap-filler-*вҶ’patch-recommendations
  given taskвҶ’prompt
  yield revised-plan, coverage-map'

  вҲҙ Merge the gap-filler results into the existing draft plan.
    Apply В«gap-filler-*вҶ’patch-recommendationsВ» to В«synthesizeвҶ’draft-planВ».
    Update the coverage map to reflect what's now covered.

    The revised-plan should be strictly better than the draft: same
    structure, more detail, fewer gaps.

  вҠЁ revised-plan is a superset of draft-plan (no information lost)
  вҠЁ coverage-map' shows fewer gaps than the original coverage-map
  вҠЁ revised-plan maintains logical consistency (no contradictions)

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- EVOLUTION LOOP: Iterate until quality converges
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠўвҲҳ evolve(synthesize, specialist-*вҶ’findings, specialist-*вҶ’recommendations, taskвҶ’prompt)
  through evaluate-completeness, spawn-gap-fillers, re-synthesize
  until evaluate-completenessвҶ’quality-score вүҘ 7
  max 3

  -- Each iteration:
  -- 1. synthesize produces draft-plan from specialist results
  -- 2. evaluate-completeness checks quality and finds gaps
  -- 3. spawn-gap-fillers creates new cells to address gaps
  -- 4. re-synthesize merges gap-filler results back into the plan
  -- 5. If quality вүҘ 7, stop. Otherwise loop: re-synthesize output
  --    becomes the new draft-plan for the next evaluation round.

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- FINAL: Polish and emit the completed plan
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠў final-plan
  given re-synthesizeвҶ’revised-plan
  given evaluate-completenessвҶ’quality-score
  given taskвҶ’prompt
  yield polished-plan, meta-summary

  вҲҙ Take В«re-synthesizeвҶ’revised-planВ» and produce the final deliverable.

    polished-plan: A clean, readable weekend itinerary for Tokyo. Include:
    - Day-by-day schedule with morning/afternoon/evening blocks
    - Specific ramen shops with what they're known for
    - Specific architecture sites with brief descriptions
    - Transit directions between locations
    - Practical tips (reservations, cash vs card, timing)

    meta-summary: Reflect on the bootstrapping process itself:
    - How many specialist cells were spawned initially?
    - How many gap-filler cells were needed?
    - What was the quality trajectory across iterations?
    - What does this say about bootstrapping from zero?

  вҠЁ polished-plan is a complete, actionable weekend itinerary
  вҠЁ polished-plan mentions ramen AND architecture in every time block
  вҠЁ meta-summary includes cell-count statistics
  вҠЁ meta-summary reflects on the bootstrapping process

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- OBSERVATIONS
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠў= bootstrapper-observations
  yield observations

  вҠў= observations вҶҗ "
    1. ZERO-START BOOTSTRAP: This program begins with no domain cells at all.
       The meta-cell (analyze-needs) inspects the task and DECIDES what cells
       to create. This is the purest form of Cell's self-bootstrapping property.

    2. TWO-PHASE SPAWNING: First wave (spawn-specialists) creates broad coverage.
       Second wave (spawn-gap-fillers) creates targeted depth. The meta-cell
       reasons about what's MISSING, not just what's NEEDED.

    3. CONVERGENCE VIA вҠўвҲҳ: The evolution loop doesn't improve a single cell вҖ”
       it improves the ENSEMBLE. Each iteration spawns new cells into the
       frontier, making the collective output more complete. The quality-score
       oracle drives convergence.

    4. TEMPLATE POLYMORPHISM: specialist-template and gap-filler-template are
       the same shape (given context вҶ’ yield findings + recommendations) but
       serve different roles. The spawner binds different purposes to the
       same interface. This is Cell's version of parametric polymorphism.

    5. META-REASONING: analyze-needs must reason about reasoning вҖ” what KINDS
       of knowledge does this task require? This is the bootstrapping insight:
       the system must be able to reflect on its own capabilities gap.

    6. MONOTONIC GROWTH: The plan only gets better. re-synthesize is a superset
       of synthesize. Information accumulates, never retracts. This matches
       Cell's monotonicity guarantee at the language level.
  "
